gomodel:SYNGO_2755  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099060 replaced by GO:0099634" , "Rationale: Fig.4: \"Ultrastructural localization of NL2 by postembedding immunogold labeling with an anti-NL2 antibody\"\n- \"At the ultrastructural level, NL2 immunogold labeling was associated with the plasma membrane at symmetric synapses (Fig. 4G) and to a lesser extent within dendrites, often onto tubular structures close to synapses\"\n\nFig.5: \"Synaptic localization of NL2 in the cerebellar cortex\"\n- \"NL2-positive structures were exactly facing synaptophysin-labeled presynaptic compartments (Fig. 5A).\"\n- \"In regions known to receive GABAergic innervation, such as Purkinje cell bodies, NL2 puncta were not colocalized with vGlut1 (Fig. 5B), whereas vGAT labeling was found always directly adjacent to NL2 (Fig. 5C). Likewise, the abundance, distribution, shape, and size of NL2-positive puncta in the glomeruli closely correlated with the vGAT staining (Fig. 5C).\"\n\nFig.6: \"Distribution of NL2 at inhibitory postsynapses in mature\ncultured hippocampal neurons\"\n\nFig.8: \"Appearance of NL2 clusters and inhibitory synaptic markers\nduring the development of hippocampal neurons in culture.\". Experimental description: - EM: \"After perfusion with a 4% paraformaldehyde/0.5% glutaraldehyde\nfixative, samples from different rat brain regions ...\"\n- in situ confocal: \"Rat brain sections were costained for NL2 and synaptophysin...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2755" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

